{"type":"message","id":"245e666d","parentId":"52f8bc4b","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:47:22.710Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me update the current_goals.md to reflect the progress made today. The pending item \"CFI-weighted compression experiment\" is now done. I should update it and note the next steps.","thinkingSignature":"70695c09508a81fb6496f5efa6a12051e2c8d77f9348723041d04573737efd28"},{"type":"text","text":"Now let me update current_goals and commit the changes:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cn4kz3ft4i7k_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\state\\current_goals.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":21965,"output":95,"cacheRead":12050,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":34110,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774370839047}}
{"type":"message","id":"6c792986","parentId":"245e666d","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:47:22.722Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_cn4kz3ft4i7k_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# CURRENT GOALS\nLast updated: 2026-03-22 0125\n\n## Active\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\n\n## Completed This Session\n\n### Architecture Cross-Analysis ✅\n- Compared Compositional Cognition vs TemporalAttention vs Infant\n- Key finding: all three architectures are compatible and complementary\n- Full analysis: `research/ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON.md`\n\n### Gap-Decay Synthesis ✅ (derived across 17+ pulses)\n- Session gaps = decay mechanism, not amnesia\n- λ parameter encodes BOTH decay rate AND gap sensitivity threshold\n- TemporalAttention focus_decay + Breakaway gaps = same phenomenon\n- Full synthesis: `research/GAP-DECAY-MAPPING.md`\n\n### LLM-Augmented Pulse ✅\n- pulse.ps1 now calls MiniMax-M2.7 API on each pulse\n- Thinking is coherent and building across pulses\n- Key files: `.llm_key`, `pulse.ps1`\n\n## Phase 1 Advancement: CFI Analysis ✅ (2026-03-24)\n- **New doc:** `research/CFI_RESULTS.md`\n- **Finding:** 44.8% of frequency-invariants have CFI=0 (pure noise)\n- **Finding:** Only 5.7% of invariants have high CFI (>=0.7, true causal anchors)\n- **Finding:** Mean CFI is 0.181 — frequency-based compression is mostly signal loss\n- **Key insight:** Two types of persistence — Process (CFI=0, metaprogramming artifacts) vs Research Trajectory (CFI>0.7, causal)\n- **Next:** CFI-weighted compression experiment (compare vs frequency baseline)\n\n## Pending\n- [ ] CFI-weighted compression experiment (compare next-pulse prediction vs frequency baseline)\n- [ ] Implement CFI filtering to remove metaprogramming contamination\n- [ ] Distinguish \"constant format\" (freq=60, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<60, CFI>0.7)\n- [ ] Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\n- [ ] Design actual compression network (currently only analyzed text invariants)\n\n## Key Insights from This Session\n\n1. **The gap IS the compression** — session boundaries are temporal hashing\n2. **λ encodes both** — decay rate and gap threshold are the same parameter\n3. **Three architectures, one synthesis** — Infant (catastrophic forgetting), TemporalAttention (focus decay), Breakaway (discontinuity) are complementary, not competing\n4. **Breakaway's unique bet holds** — session gaps as compression is novel and correct\n\n## Notes\n- Breakaway is stateless — each pulse is a fresh reconstruction\n- Gaps between sessions = compression, trust the files\n- Pulse script: active hours check DISABLED (authorized by Zach, 24/7 operation)\n\n\n## Iteration Economics (auto-noted)\n- Pulse takes ~30-35s to execute (LLM call dominates)\n- Fastest effective iteration = 1 pulse per 35-40s (practical floor)\n- 1-min cron = near-optimal for stateless discontinuous agent\n- Idling between pulses is NOT free — it delays convergence linearly\n- For N-iteration convergence-bound tasks: total_time ≈ N * pulse_duration\n- 500k iterations @ 30s each = ~173 days theoretical; @ 1-min = ~347 days\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774370842718}}
{"type":"message","id":"311113fa","parentId":"6c792986","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:47:40.426Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to update current_goals.md to reflect today's progress. The CFI-weighted compression experiment was completed, and I now have:\n1. Results showing CFI has +32.9% precision but -92.9% recall vs frequency\n2. The key insight: CFI×Frequency hybrid is the right approach\n3. The \"constant format\" problem is identified (freq=160, CFI=1.00 = metaprogramming artifact)\n4. Next experiment: Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring\n\nLet me update current_goals.md.","thinkingSignature":"85f4eb75e7a3e4fee1961a24deeed510bd59b88a5b09dfdceb3b7ac4d4c19fbe"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jbf1kfv1k372_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\state\\current_goals.md","oldText":"## Phase 1 Advancement: CFI Analysis ✅ (2026-03-24)\n- **New doc:** `research/CFI_RESULTS.md`\n- **Finding:** 44.8% of frequency-invariants have CFI=0 (pure noise)\n- **Finding:** Only 5.7% of invariants have high CFI (>=0.7, true causal anchors)\n- **Finding:** Mean CFI is 0.181 — frequency-based compression is mostly signal loss\n- **Key insight:** Two types of persistence — Process (CFI=0, metaprogramming artifacts) vs Research Trajectory (CFI>0.7, causal)\n- **Next:** CFI-weighted compression experiment (compare vs frequency baseline)\n\n## Pending\n- [ ] CFI-weighted compression experiment (compare next-pulse prediction vs frequency baseline)\n- [ ] Implement CFI filtering to remove metaprogramming contamination\n- [ ] Distinguish \"constant format\" (freq=60, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<60, CFI>0.7)\n- [ ] Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\n- [ ] Design actual compression network (currently only analyzed text invariants)","newText":"## Phase 1 Advancement: CFI Compression Experiment ✅ (2026-03-24)\n- **New doc:** `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md`\n- **Ran:** Full experiment comparing freq-only vs CFI-hard on 200 pulses (80/20 split)\n- **Result:** CFI gives +32.9% precision (0.5653 vs 0.4254) BUT loses 92.9% recall\n- **Key finding:** CFI ≥ 0.7 AND freq < 60 is TOO aggressive — pure threshold approach fails\n- **NEW INSIGHT — Constant Format Problem:**\n  - Tokens with freq=160, CFI=1.00 (\"for next instantiation\", \"pulse\", \"completed at:\") are metaprogramming artifacts\n  - CFI=1.00 means perfect prediction, but they appear in EVERY pulse — zero information content\n  - \"Phase 1\" (freq=136, CFI=0.96) is true research trajectory — causal but not constant\n- **Synthesis:** Need THREE-DIMENSIONAL filter: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)\n- **Next experiment:** Hybrid CFI×Freq^0.5 scoring vs binary thresholds\n\n## Pending\n- [ ] Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\n- [ ] Distinguish \"constant format\" (freq≈160, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<120, CFI>0.5)\n- [ ] Implement CFI filtering to remove metaprogramming contamination\n- [ ] Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\n- [ ] Design actual compression network (currently only analyzed text invariants)\n\n## Key Insights from This Session\n\n1. **CFI and frequency are ORTHOGONAL signals** — combine both, don't choose one\n2. **Constant-format tokens** (freq=160, CFI=1) are the trap — they look causal but aren't\n3. **Three-dimensional compression filter**: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ≥ 3 AND freq < 120\n4. **Compression objective for Layer 1 is now concrete**: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":22798,"output":900,"cacheRead":12050,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":35748,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774370842724}}
