{"type":"message","id":"018dd122","parentId":"a4fadafd","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:47:54.620Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_juspas08orma_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[master f678b32] CFI compression experiment: CFI gives +33% precision but -93% recall vs freq-only\n 4 files changed, 746 insertions(+), 9 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 experiments/cfi_compression/experiment_results.md\n create mode 100644 research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md\n create mode 100644 scripts/cfi_compression_experiment.py"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1500,"aggregated":"[master f678b32] CFI compression experiment: CFI gives +33% precision but -93% recall vs freq-only\n 4 files changed, 746 insertions(+), 9 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 experiments/cfi_compression/experiment_results.md\n create mode 100644 research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md\n create mode 100644 scripts/cfi_compression_experiment.py","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774370874617}}
{"type":"message","id":"9f4027ea","parentId":"018dd122","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:48:05.873Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, the commit was successful. Now let me provide a summary of what was done.","thinkingSignature":"7937b995b1c97cc1118bfa534fad6f362fe529a288aa8b8852b43a2209e1f70f"},{"type":"text","text":"**Report:**\n\n## What I Did\n\n### Research (Primary)\nImplemented and ran the **CFI-weighted compression experiment** that was pending from the previous session. The experiment compared:\n- **Strategy A (freq-only):** Keep tokens appearing ≥3 pulses\n- **Strategy B (CFI-hard):** Keep tokens with CFI ≥ 0.7 AND frequency < 60\n\n**Key empirical results:**\n- CFI wins precision: **+32.9%** (0.5653 vs 0.4254) — filters noise\n- Freq wins recall: **+92.9%** (0.1819 vs 0.0128) — captures more signal\n- CFI-hard was **too aggressive**: only 25 tokens vs 484 for freq\n\n### The Key Finding: Constant Format Problem\n\nDiscovered that the freq=160/CFI=1.00 tokens (\"for next instantiation\", \"pulse\", \"completed at:\") are **metaprogramming artifacts** — they appear in every single pulse and predict perfectly, but carry zero research signal. Pure CFI threshold can't distinguish these from true research trajectory tokens like \"phase 1\" (freq=136, CFI=0.96).\n\n### The Synthesis: Three-Dimensional Compression\n\nCFI and frequency are **orthogonal signals**. Neither alone is sufficient. The real compression objective is:\n\n```\nKeep token T if: CFI(T) ≥ 0.5 AND freq(T) ≥ 3 AND freq(T) < 120\n```\n\nThis filters constant-format artifacts while preserving genuine research trajectory.\n\n## What I Learned\n1. **CFI ≥ 0.7 is too aggressive** — need a softer CFI threshold (0.5) \n2. **Frequency alone is noisy** — 44.8% of freq-invariants have CFI=0\n3. **The answer is hybrid** — CFI × frequency scoring, not binary thresholds\n4. **Commit:** f678b32\n\n## Next Experiment\nDesign **Strategy C (Hybrid):** `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, frequency(T) / 120)` — should beat both A and B simultaneously by preserving precision AND recall."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":24232,"output":480,"cacheRead":12050,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":36762,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774370874622}}
